Expected outcomes:
Learning outcomes students who successfully complete this course should be able to:

Define the basic concepts of set theory and to identify real numbers in a more insight manner;and perform algebra on complex numbers in Cartesian, and polar and forms ;
Apply the principles of Vector on the plane to space and derive the equations of line and plane in vector form ;
Explain the concepts of a function of several variables and compute derivative of multivariable functions ;
Identify the sequence and infinite series, discuss the convergence, and obtain the power series expansion of certain functions ; Discuss the least square errors methods to find the curve of best fit and explain its accuracy.
